              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Line Counter – FAQ</h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    How does this line counter work?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    The tool reads your text, normalizes line endings, splits it
                    into lines, and then classifies each line as empty or
                    non-empty. It also counts characters and words. All of this
                    happens instantly in your browser as you type or paste
                    content.
                  </p>
                </details>
                <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    What counts as a line?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    A line is any sequence of characters ending with a newline
                    character. The last line is counted even if it does not end
                    with a newline. The counter supports Windows (CRLF),
                    Unix/Linux (LF), and old Mac (CR) styles.
                  </p>
                </details>
                <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    What is the difference between total lines and non-empty
                    lines?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    Total lines includes every line, including blank ones.
                    Non-empty lines only include lines that contain at least one
                    non-whitespace character after trimming spaces and tabs.
                    Empty lines are those that become empty after trimming.
                  </p>
                </details>
                <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    Is my text or code stored anywhere?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    No. The line counter is implemented in JavaScript and runs
                    locally in your browser. Your content is not uploaded,
                    logged, or stored on a server.
